This paper is about compressing word embeddings for NLP models, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the relationship between compression quality and downstream performance, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions logistic regression, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS).
